org.hl7.cdsdt.r2

Class CD

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hl7.cdsdt.r2.HXIT
      • org.hl7.cdsdt.r2.ANY
        • org.hl7.cdsdt.r2.CD

  • public class CD
extends ANY
    A CD is a reference to a concept defined in an external code system, terminology, or ontology. A CD may also contain an original text or phrase that served as the basis of the coding.

    Java class for CD complex type.

    The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 

     <complexType name="CD">
   <complexContent>
     <extension base="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}ANY">
       <sequence>
         <element name="displayName" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}ST" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="originalText" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}ST" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="translation" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}CD" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"/>
       </sequence>
       <attribute name="code" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}Code" />
       <attribute name="codeSystem" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}Uid" />
       <attribute name="codeSystemName" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" />
       <attribute name="codeSystemVersion" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" />
       <attribute name="valueSet" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}Uid" />
       <attribute name="valueSetVersion" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" />
     </extension>
   </complexContent>
 </complexType>

      • getTranslation

        public List<CD> getTranslation()
        Gets the value of the translation property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the translation property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getTranslation().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list CD
